The paper deals with a problem of recovering the support of data samples from random linear projections, which is a common problem in information theory (cs.IT) and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of subgaussian prior is a common technique in both fields. The paper also involves a theoretical analysis of the sample complexity, which is a common topic in theoretical computer science (cs.DS) and statistics (cs.SI). Finally, the proposed estimator has a computational complexity, which is a common topic in numerical analysis (cs.NA).
